RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 1 1M Turf CR: 77. Maiden Claiming Purse 16000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 123 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000, if for $18,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CAPIAT was a bit hard to load prior to the start, was off slowly and spotted the field to begin, tracked the early pace from the inside, improved position along the backstretch run, ran in pursuit of the pacesetter two wide into the far turn, made a steady advance on SHAUN'S JAZZ into the stretch, wore down that rival in the final sixteenth and held in a drive for the win. SHAUN'S JAZZ assumed command away from the start, set decent fractions while controlling the pace into the backstretch run, was well handled while setting all of the pace to the far turn, extended the lead at the quarter marker, set down for the drive and was confronted by CAPIAT inside of the furlong pole, battled with CAPIAT into the final sixteenth, was bested in deep stretch and was clear in the end for second. GRACEFUL MISCHIEF was unhurried away from the start, slipped to the inside and saved ground into the backstretch run, was content to trail to the half-mile marker, improved position two wide into the far turn, swung to the four path into upper stretch, was not able to impact the top pair but offered a late bid and was up in the final strides to secure third. BLUEGRASS RYDER was asked to rate off of the early leaders, became rank and hard to place into the first turn, was steered to the three path nearing the backstretch run and carried out VINNIEBOB at that station, settled into the backstretch and tracked the decent pace between runners to the half-mile marker, maintained a two wide path into the far turn, slipped to the inside nearing the top of the lane, mounted an inside bid at mid-stretch, could not sustain that run into the final sixteenth, weakened and was outfinished for third. VINNIEBOB settled in the second flight to begin, tracked the early pace three wide then was carried four wide into the backstretch run, tracked the decent pace three to four wide approaching the half-mile marker, lost position into the far turn, swung five wide into the stretch and gave way. THECHIEFHASTRICKS was forwardly placed away from the start, stalked the decent early pace from a two wide position along the first turn, prompted the pace to the half-mile pole, raced three wide into the far turn and lost position at the quarter marker, chased three wide into the stretch and faded in the final furlong.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: LOOKOUT POINT was content to let the pace scenario play out in front a lagged a few lengths behind the field through the early going, was put into a drive from the seven-sixteenths pole, lengthened stride, swung five wide into the stretch with a lot of ground to make up, produced a bold rally and reeled in KO SAMUI (IRE) in the final yards. KO SAMUI (IRE) settled from the break then moved forwardly tipping out to the three path through clubhouse turn, remained three to four wide through the backstretch run rating well as the rider dictated, moved challenge for the lead with a forward move through the far turn, responded when set down at the quarter pole, took a short lead passing the three-sixteenths pole then was unable fend off LOOKOUT POINT in sight of the wire. MY DAD IS THIRSTY broke well, was pushed to go for the lead two deep going into the first turn, opened up a short lead passing the seven-eighths pole then had some pressure applied by EFFECTIVE GIG within a furlong, went on with it when that foe was content to drop back to a stalking position, held sway into the far turn, was challenged by that rival passing the five-sixteenths but battled back, then had to deal with an additional bid from KO SAMUI (IRE) continued on with good courage but was outfinished in the final furlong. EFFECTIVE GIG broke well then ceded the early lead to MY DAD IS THIRSTY, decided to press the pace with six furlongs to run when KO SAMUI (IRE) also decided to press the issue, then eased back a bit down the backstretch allowing MY DAD IS THIRSTY to dictate the pace to the far turn, was set down and sent to challenge for the lead near the three furlong pole, had that bid rebuffed then had to battle between horses turning for home could not sustain the bid and weakened in the late stages.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 3 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 75. Maiden Special Weight Purse 30000. FOR MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. RACE.FOOTNOTES: CLEVER CLOVER broke in at the start and was off a step slowly, recovered and showed speed in the early going, contested the fast pace inside of a pair of rivals into the turn, carved out quick fractions while pressed to the quarter pole, shook free into the stretch and drew clear at the furlong grounds, felt pressure from the runner-up inside of the sixteenth-marker, dug in in the final strides and just lasted for the win at the finish. HERMELINDA'S FANCY tracked the fast early pace from the inside, saved all of the ground into the turn and was well placed approaching the top of the lane, chased CLEVER CLOVER to mid-stretch and made a mild gain at the furlong pole, tipped to the two path into deep stretch, rallied and just missed for the win, while besting the rest. ELEGANT BOY took back leaving the start and was unhurried in the early stages, raced three wide into the turn, was floated out by BIG BET nearing the quarter marker and swung five wide for the drive, closed in the final furlong, could not impact the top two in deep stretch and was clear in the end for third. BIG BET chased the fast early pace from a two wide path, gained ground into the turn, shifted four wide nearing the quarter marker and floated out ELEGANT BOY, maintained a four wide path into the stretch, lost ground at the furlong marker, lacked a response in the final sixteenth and weakened in deep stretch. REGAL REDWOOD showed speed and disputed the fast early pace, was engaged by CLEVER CLOVER and contested the fast pace between runners into the turn, pressed CLEVER CLOVER two wide to the quarter marker, lost position into the stretch and gave way. RAMATHORN broke alertly and contested the quick early pace, pressed the pace three wide into the turn, lost position nearing the quarter marker, maintained a three wide path into the stretch and tired in the final furlong.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: COUNCILWOMAN JILLY was away in good order and was forwardly placed into the first turn, kept close attendance to the pacesetter into the backstretch run and prompted the decent pace to the half-mile marker, pressured PROOF OF JAZZ into the far turn and battled with that rival into the stretch, took a narrow lead at the furlong marker, responded to firm urging and dug in into the final sixteenth, held foes at bay into deep stretch and determinedly prevailed at the finish. RIVETING SPIRIT settled just off of the early pace and raced a bit in tight into the first turn, tracked the decent pace two wide and between runners to the half-mile pole, chased between and two wide to the quarter marker, advanced into upper stretch and raced within aim nearing the furlong grounds, tipped four wide into the final sixteenth, rallied in traffic and missed for the win at the finish, while earning the nod for second on the wire. PROOF OF JAZZ broke alertly and assumed command away from the start, showed the way into the first turn and set solid fractions while prompted through the backstretch run, was pressured into the far turn by COUNCILWOMAN JILLY and battled with that rival into the stretch, lost ground to COUNCILWOMAN JILLY inside of the furlong marker, re-rallied into the final sixteenth, was gamely bested in the final strides and was just edged for second on the wire. REBEL GIRL bobbled leaving the start and was away a step slowly, was allowed to settle in the early stages and saved ground into the first turn, tracked the pace while not far back heading to the quarter marker, chased from the two path along the far turn and swung four wide into the stretch, made a mild gain at the furlong pole, shifted six wide into the final sixteenth, closed willingly and just missed for third on the wire. BUYBACK tracked the early pace from the inside, improved position along the backstretch run and stalked from the inside heading to the far turn, chased the leaders to the quarter marker, raced in tight into upper stretch and lacked room nearing the furlong grounds, found a seam into the final sixteenth and was outfinished in deep stretch. TOPANTICIPATION (GB) settled just off of the early leaders and raced a bit in tight into the first turn, tracked the pace three wide into the backstretch run, was well placed heading into the far turn, maintained a three wide path into the stretch, ran evenly to the furlong pole, shifted to the five path into the final sixteenth, was squeezed by oncoming rivals in deep stretch and was outkicked in the final strides.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: WINE AND WHISKY broke alertly and assumed command away from the start, set the pace into the first turn and was prompted through decent fractions along the backstretch run, was pressured into the far turn and carved out the pace to the quarter pole, shook free into the stretch and was kept to task into the final sixteenth, determinedly dug in in the late stages and held in a drive at the finish. HEAT N REHEAT tracked the early pace from the inside, raced close to the decent pace along the backstretch run and saved ground into the far turn, offered an inside bid into the stretch and vied for the lead nearing the furlong marker, battled into deep stretch but could not make headway on the winner in the final stages, was outfinished and just held for second at the wire. SUGAR BEETS was allowed to settle leaving the start, tracked the decent pace three wide through the backstretch run while not far back, raced three wide into the far turn and was roused five wide into the stretch, ran evenly to the furlong grounds, rallied in the final sixteenth, just missed for second on the wire and was up in time to secure third. HARMON tracked the early pace three wide into the first turn, maintained an outside path through the backstretch run and stalked the pace to the half-mile marker, was well positioned three wide nearing the quarter pole, swung to the four path into the stretch and lost ground at the furlong marker, re-rallied into the final sixteenth, raced in a bit of late traffic in deep stretch, was outkicked and just missed for third at the finish. GROWTH ENGINE was prominent in the early going, stalked the pacesetter along the first turn then advanced and prompted the decent pace through the backstretch run, pressed WINE AND WHISKY to the quarter pole, lost ground nearing mid-stretch, could not keep pace into the final sixteenth and weakened in deep stretch. BUENISIMO lunged leaving the start and was away a bit slowly, settled along the inside into the first turn, saved ground through the backstretch run and advanced heading to the half-mile pole, chased along the far turn and angled four wide into the stretch, lost position at the furlong marker and did not offer a late response. CALI CONQUEST was forwardly placed leaving the start and tracked between rivals into the first turn, raced in tight nearing the six-furlong pole and was shuffled back into the backstretch run, tracked two wide and between runners heading to the half-mile marker, lost ground two wide along the far turn and tired in the stretch drive.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHIC SAMARAI came away well, ceded the pacesetting duties to GENTLE JULIA then stalked that one while being well-handled, responded when asked to quicken passing the three furlong marker then was set down in earnest at the top of the stretch, quickly put some distance on the field and finished strong despite racing on the wrong lead. RACE.FOOTNOTES: SPICE was forwardly placed away from the start and tracked the solid early pace from the inside, lost ground along the turn and chased from the inside heading to the quarter pole, saved all of the ground into the stretch, ran evenly while within aim approaching the furlong marker, responded to urging into the final sixteenth and tipped two wide into deep stretch, surged in the final strides and got up at the finish to prevail. RACE.FOOTNOTES: IL CAPITANO broke well and got a clear run to the lead into the first turn, set a solid pace while always traveling well in hand, repelled a bit from stablemate LIL MIRACLE MAN at the top of the stretch, and plenty in reserve and sprinted away under intermittent urging. HOUSE OF LORDS lagged well behind the field for the first half mile, hugged the rail through the far turn, waited patiently for room, slipped through an opening along the rail turning into the stretch, was not able to impact the winner in the late stages and got up for second. RESPECT THE HUSTLE was outrun into the first turn but held the rail while tracking the pace through the first half mile, bided time through the far turn while holding position waiting for clear running, got clear in mid stretch, was outfinished in deep stretch and was just edged for second in the final strides. RACE.FOOTNOTES: SHARONA'S WILD BOY had to be pushed a bit to keep up with the early pace, chased the two pacesetters through the turn, tipped out to the four to five path for the stretch run and ran on well under strong handling to get up in time. GOLDENSUNRISE bobbled slightly at the break but recovered quickly and was set off for the lead, took over the pacesetting duties under a stout hold with GOLDENCENTS pressing the issue to the outside, disposed of that one at the top of the stretch while still in hand, opened up passing the three sixteenths marker, kept on with good courage and just failed to last while drifting out in deep stretch. ELCONDOR broke well, moved over towards the inside once clear, pressed GOLDENSUNRISE to the turn, bid for the lead from the three-furlong pole but had that bid repelled, came into the stretch under heavy pressure but weakened passing the furlong pole. ALMOST SNOW sat behind the early pace while saving ground throughout, dropped back a few lengths passing the half mile pole then came back on with a run through the turn, was running on well up the rail in the stretch then weakened in the final furlong.
